 basic commands by using “help”
msf > help
--------------------------------------
 “show payloads”. It lists all the available payloads in alphabetic order.
msf > show payloads
--------------------------------------------------------------------------
“show exploits”. It lists all the available payloads in alphabetic order and
it also shows the date it was disclosed and the rank of the exploit ranging from “Excellent-average”.
msf > show exploits
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
“show auxiliary”. As mentioned earlier, auxiliary modules include scanners, denial of service modules, fuzzers, and more.
msf > show auxiliary
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
“show post”. Post modules are used for post exploitation that is used on a compromised target machine to gather evidence or pivot deep within the network.
msf > show post
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
“show encoder”. These are used to obfuscate modules to avoid detection by a protection mechanism such as an antivirus or a firewall.
msf > show encoders
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
“show nops”. They are used to keep the size of payload consistent across exploit attempts.
msf > show nops
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
